purchases
for
the
first
6
months
(1
point
per
dollar
thereafter)
Balance
Transfer
Fee:
Introductory
fee
of
either
$5
or
3%
of
the
amount
of
each
balance
transfer,
whichever
is
greater,
for
120
days
from
account
opening.
After
that,
up
to
5%
for
each
balance
transfer,
with
a
minimum
of
$5.
Rewards:
Earn
1
point
per
dollar
spent
on
purchases
with
your
card.
Other
Benefits
and
Drawbacks:
Although
it
doesn’t
offer
a
traditional
welcome
bonus,
the
earning
potential
within
the
first
six
months
of
owning
the
card
could
be
just
as
valuable.
Points
can
be
pooled
with
other
Wells
Fargo
cards
and
redeemed
for
50%
more
value
for
airfare
when
booked
through
the
Go
Far
Rewards
website.
As
a
Visa
Signature
card,
the
Wells
Fargo
Platinum
Visa
also
offers
trip
cancellation
protection
and
lost
luggage
reimbursement,
travel
accident
insurance
and
auto
rental
collision
coverage.
Read
our
full
review
of
the
Wells
Fargo
Visa
Signature
card
.
